{"word":"ἐνθάδε","slug":"ἐνθάδε","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἐνϑάδε</el></b> [<el>ἔνϑα</el> ‘there’, <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:δέ\">δέ</a></el>] <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ adv.\">adv.</a> expressing position relatively near the speaker <b>here<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> verb of motion <b><a href='B:500 4:15'>J 4:15f</a></b> (= to this place); <b><a href='B:510 25:17'>Ac 25:17</a></b> (= at this place)<b>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> without verb of motion in this place <b><a href='B:490 24:41'>Lk 24:41</a>; <a href='B:510 10:18'>Ac 10:18</a></b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ freq.\">freq.</a> in Ac. <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἐνέχω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἔνθεν\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}